%h1 Avoiding Scams
%p
  %span{:style => "background-color: #ffff99;"}
    %strong> Deal locally, face-to-face
    —follow this one rule and avoid 99% of scam attempts.
%ul
  %li
    %strong Do not extend payment to anyone you have not met in person.
  %li
    %strong> Beware offers involving shipping -
    deal with locals you can meet in person.
  %li
    %strong Never wire funds (e.g. Western Union)
    \- anyone who asks you to is a scammer.
  %li
    %strong Don't accept cashier/certified checks or money orders
    \- banks cash fakes, then hold you responsible.
  %li
    %strong> Transactions are between users only
    , no third party provides a "guarantee".
  %li
    %strong Never give out financial info
    (bank account, social security, paypal account, etc).
  %li
    %strong> Do not rent or purchase sight-unseen
    —that amazing "deal" may not exist.
  %li
    %strong Refuse background/credit checks
    until you have met landlord/employer in person.
